<TITLE> Quayes to take office as foreign secy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 8 (bdnews24.com)Ambassador Mohamed Mijarul Quayes arrived in Dhaka Wednesday to take charge as acting foreign secretary. "The handing over ceremony is set for 4pm," Md Touhid Hossain, the outgoing foreign secretary, told bdnews24.com. Hossain, who was appointed acting foreign secretary on Dec 17 2006 and later foreign secretary by the immediate past caretaker government, has been made principal of the Foreign Service Academy, he said. Quayes was serving as Bangladesh ambassador to Russia when he was selected for the new position.
